Activity-in-Diagram: Strip

Description

Notes:
See A3333 and A333.

Definitions:
Stripping - an aqueous solution or other medium used to reverse the extraction process, transferring a target metal from the organic phase back into the aqueous phase in a purified and concentrated form. Adapted from US5228903A (see references).

Standards:

References:
See A3333 and A333.

O’Keefe, T. J. (1993). Method for stripping metals in solvent extraction (U.S. Patent No. 5228903 A). U.S. Patent and Trademark Office.
